---
import Layout from '../../layouts/Layout.astro';
---

<Layout title="Screen Repair | Jake Fixes Tech — Littleton, NH"
description="Laptop, Chromebook, all-in-one and handheld gaming console screen replacement. Free quote, honest advice, $100 labor plus parts. Serving Littleton NH and the North Country.">

  <!-- Header Banner -->
  <section style="position:relative;overflow:hidden;background-color:rgb(30,64,175);">
    <img src="/hero.jpg" alt="Professional tech workspace with dual monitors" fetchpriority="high" decoding="async" style="position:absolute;inset:0;width:100%;height:100%;object-fit:cover;z-index:0;" />
    <div style="position:absolute;inset:0;background:linear-gradient(135deg,rgba(30,64,175,0.88),rgba(37,99,235,0.88));z-index:1;"></div>
    <div style="max-width:56rem;margin:0 auto;padding:4rem 1.5rem;text-align:center;position:relative;z-index:2;">
      <p style="font-size:0.875rem;font-weight:600;text-transform:uppercase;letter-spacing:0.1em;color:#93c5fd;">
        <a href="/services" style="color:#93c5fd;text-decoration:none;" aria-label="Back to all services">← Services</a>
      </p>
      <h1 style="margin-top:0.75rem;font-size:2.5rem;font-weight:800;color:white;line-height:1.2;">Screen Repair</h1>
      <p style="margin-top:1rem;color:#bfdbfe;line-height:1.75;font-size:1.1rem;max-width:42rem;margin-left:auto;margin-right:auto;">
        Cracked, flickering or completely dead screen? I replace screens on laptops, Chromebooks, all-in-one computers and handheld gaming consoles, including retro handhelds. Free quote, honest advice.
      </p>
      <div style="margin-top:1.5rem;display:flex;flex-wrap:wrap;justify-content:center;gap:1rem;">
        <a href="/contact" style="display:inline-flex;align-items:center;gap:0.5rem;background:white;color:#1e40af;font-weight:700;padding:0.75rem 1.75rem;border-radius:0.5rem;text-decoration:none;font-size:1rem;">
          Get a Free Quote
          <svg style="height:1rem;width:1rem;" aria-hidden="true" fill="none" viewBox="0 0 24 24" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2"><path d="M5 12h14M12 5l7 7-7 7"/></svg>
        </a>
        <a href="/pricing" style="display:inline-flex;align-items:center;gap:0.5rem;background:rgba(255,255,255,0.15);color:white;font-weight:600;padding:0.75rem 1.75rem;border-radius:0.5rem;text-decoration:none;font-size:1rem;border:1px solid rgba(255,255,255,0.3);">
          View Pricing
        </a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Info Bar -->
  <section style="background:#1e40af;padding:1.25rem 1.5rem;">
    <div style="max-width:56rem;margin:0 auto;display:flex;flex-wrap:wrap;align-items:center;justify-content:center;gap:2rem;text-align:center;">
      <div>
        <div style="font-size:1.75rem;font-weight:800;color:white;">$100</div>
        <div style="font-size:0.8rem;color:#bfdbfe;font-weight:600;">Labor + Parts</div>
      </div>
      <div style="width:1px;height:2.5rem;background:rgba(255,255,255,0.2);flex-shrink:0;"></div>
      <div>
        <div style="font-size:1.75rem;font-weight:800;color:white;">Free Quote</div>
        <div style="font-size:0.8rem;color:#bfdbfe;font-weight:600;">Fast Turnaround</div>
      </div>
      <div style="width:1px;height:2.5rem;background:rgba(255,255,255,0.2);flex-shrink:0;"></div>
      <div>
        <div style="font-size:1.75rem;font-weight:800;color:white;">30 Day</div>
        <div style="font-size:0.8rem;color:#bfdbfe;font-weight:600;">Labor Warranty</div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- What I Replace -->
  <section style="background:#f8fafc;padding:4rem 1.5rem;">
    <div style="max-width:56rem;margin:0 auto;">
      <div style="margin-bottom:2.5rem;">
        <p style="font-size:0.875rem;font-weight:600;text-transform:uppercase;letter-spacing:0.1em;color:#2563eb;">What I Work On</p>
        <h2 style="font-size:2rem;font-weight:800;color:#111827;margin-top:0.5rem;">Screens I Replace</h2>
        <p style="color:#6b7280;margin-top:0.75rem;line-height:1.75;">If your screen is cracked, dead, flickering, showing lines, or just not turning on, reach out and let me know what you have. Most screens I can source and replace quickly.</p>
      </div>

      <div style="display:flex;flex-direction:column;gap:1rem;">

        <div class="service-item" style="border-left:4px solid #2563eb;">
          <div class="service-num" style="background:#eff6ff;color:#1e40af;">
            <svg fill="none" viewBox="0 0 24 24" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2"><rect x="2" y="3" width="20" height="14" rx="2"/><line x1="8" y1="21" x2="16" y2="21"/><line x1="12" y1="17" x2="12" y2="21"/></svg>
          </div>
          <div>
            <h3 class="item-title">Laptops &amp; Chromebooks</h3>
            <p class="item-desc">Windows, Linux and Chrome OS laptops of all makes and models, including all Chromebooks. Cracked glass, dead backlights, flickering displays, lines across the screen. I source the correct replacement panel and swap it out. Note: MacBook screen replacements are not available as I do not work on Apple hardware.</p>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="service-item" style="border-left:4px solid #7c3aed;">
          <div class="service-num" style="background:#f5f3ff;color:#6d28d9;">
            <svg fill="none" viewBox="0 0 24 24" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2"><rect x="2" y="3" width="20" height="14" rx="2"/><path d="M8 21h8M12 17v4"/><path d="M7 8h.01M12 8h.01"/><circle cx="17" cy="8" r="1"/></svg>
          </div>
          <div>
            <h3 class="item-title">All-in-One Computers</h3>
            <p class="item-desc">All-in-one desktops where the screen and computer are built into one unit. These can be trickier to disassemble than laptops but I have experience with the process. Windows and Linux only, no iMac repairs.</p>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="service-item" style="border-left:4px solid #15803d;">
          <div class="service-num" style="background:#f0fdf4;color:#15803d;">
            <svg fill="none" viewBox="0 0 24 24" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2"><rect x="2" y="6" width="20" height="12" rx="2"/><path d="M6 12h.01M10 12h.01M7 9l-1 3 1 3M13 9l1 3-1 3"/></svg>
          </div>
          <div>
            <h3 class="item-title">Handheld Gaming Consoles</h3>
            <p class="item-desc">Nintendo Switch, Switch Lite, Steam Deck, Game Boy, older Nintendo handhelds and other retro handheld consoles. If it has a screen and fits in your hands, ask me. Chances are I can replace it.</p>
          </div>
        </div>

      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- What I Don't Do -->
  <section style="background:white;padding:4rem 1.5rem;">
    <div style="max-width:56rem;margin:0 auto;">
      <div style="margin-bottom:2rem;">
        <p style="font-size:0.875rem;font-weight:600;text-transform:uppercase;letter-spacing:0.1em;color:#2563eb;">Honest Limitations</p>
        <h2 style="font-size:2rem;font-weight:800;color:#111827;margin-top:0.5rem;">What I Don't Replace</h2>
        <p style="color:#6b7280;margin-top:0.75rem;line-height:1.75;">I'd rather be upfront than have you bring something in that I can't help with. Here's what's outside my scope right now.</p>
      </div>
      <div style="display:flex;flex-direction:column;gap:1rem;">

        <div class="limit-item">
          <div class="limit-icon" aria-hidden="true">
            <svg fill="none" viewBox="0 0 24 24" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2"><rect x="5" y="2" width="14" height="20" rx="2"/><line x1="12" y1="18" x2="12.01" y2="18"/></svg>
          </div>
          <div>
            <h3>Phones</h3>
            <p>Phone screen replacement requires specialized heat tools and equipment I don't currently have. The compact, tightly assembled nature of modern phones means attempting it without the right tools risks further damage. I plan to offer this service in the future.</p>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="limit-item">
          <div class="limit-icon" aria-hidden="true">
            <svg fill="none" viewBox="0 0 24 24" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2"><rect x="2" y="4" width="20" height="16" rx="2"/><line x1="8" y1="20" x2="16" y2="20"/></svg>
          </div>
          <div>
            <h3>Tablets</h3>
            <p>Tablets fall into the same category as phones. Tightly bonded screens with specialized tooling requirements. Not something I take on currently.</p>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="limit-item">
          <div class="limit-icon" aria-hidden="true">
            <svg fill="none" viewBox="0 0 24 24" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2"><rect x="2" y="3" width="20" height="14" rx="2"/><path d="M8 21h8M12 17v4"/><path d="M7 8h.01M12 8h.01"/><circle cx="17" cy="8" r="1"/></svg>
          </div>
          <div>
            <h3>Apple Hardware</h3>
            <p>MacBooks, iMacs and other Apple hardware are outside my scope entirely. For Apple hardware repairs, Apple or an Apple Authorized Service Provider is the right call.</p>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="limit-item">
          <div class="limit-icon" aria-hidden="true">
            <svg fill="none" viewBox="0 0 24 24" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2"><rect x="2" y="3" width="20" height="14" rx="2"/><line x1="2" y1="20" x2="22" y2="20"/></svg>
          </div>
          <div>
            <h3>Standalone Computer Monitors</h3>
            <p>External desktop monitors are generally not worth repairing. Replacement panels often cost more than a new monitor. If your standalone monitor is dead, a new one is almost always the better financial decision.</p>
          </div>
        </div>

      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Honest Advice -->
  <section style="background:#f8fafc;padding:4rem 1.5rem;">
    <div style="max-width:56rem;margin:0 auto;">
      <div style="margin-bottom:2rem;">
        <p style="font-size:0.875rem;font-weight:600;text-transform:uppercase;letter-spacing:0.1em;color:#2563eb;">Before You Repair</p>
        <h2 style="font-size:2rem;font-weight:800;color:#111827;margin-top:0.5rem;">Is It Worth Fixing?</h2>
        <p style="color:#6b7280;margin-top:0.75rem;line-height:1.75;">I will always give you an honest answer on this. Not every repair makes financial sense and I would rather tell you that upfront than take your money for something that isn't worth it.</p>
      </div>

      <div style="display:grid;gap:1.25rem;grid-template-columns:1fr 1fr;">
        <div style="background:white;border:2px solid #86efac;border-radius:0.75rem;padding:1.5rem;">
          <div style="display:flex;align-items:center;gap:0.75rem;margin-bottom:1rem;">
            <div style="display:flex;height:2.5rem;width:2.5rem;align-items:center;justify-content:center;border-radius:0.5rem;background:#dcfce7;color:#15803d;flex-shrink:0;" aria-hidden="true">
              <svg fill="none" viewBox="0 0 24 24" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2"><polyline points="20 6 9 17 4 12"/></svg>
            </div>
            <h3 style="font-size:1rem;font-weight:700;color:#15803d;margin:0;">Generally Worth Fixing</h3>
          </div>
          <p style="font-size:0.875rem;color:#374151;line-height:1.7;margin:0;">If the repair cost is roughly a third or less of what the device costs new, it usually makes sense to fix it. You get your familiar device back, your data stays intact, and you save money compared to buying new.</p>
        </div>
        <div style="background:white;border:2px solid #fca5a5;border-radius:0.75rem;padding:1.5rem;">
          <div style="display:flex;align-items:center;gap:0.75rem;margin-bottom:1rem;">
            <div style="display:flex;height:2.5rem;width:2.5rem;align-items:center;justify-content:center;border-radius:0.5rem;background:#fee2e2;color:#dc2626;flex-shrink:0;" aria-hidden="true">
              <svg fill="none" viewBox="0 0 24 24" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2"><line x1="18" y1="6" x2="6" y2="18"/><line x1="6" y1="6" x2="18" y2="18"/></svg>
            </div>
            <h3 style="font-size:1rem;font-weight:700;color:#dc2626;margin:0;">Probably Not Worth It</h3>
          </div>
          <p style="font-size:0.875rem;color:#374151;line-height:1.7;margin:0;">If the repair cost is approaching half or more of what the device costs new, it's usually smarter to put that money toward a replacement instead. I'll tell you this honestly before you spend a dime.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Not Sure? Just Ask -->
  <section style="background:white;padding:4rem 1.5rem;">
    <div style="max-width:56rem;margin:0 auto;">
      <div style="background:#eff6ff;border:2px solid #bfdbfe;border-radius:0.75rem;padding:2rem;display:flex;align-items:flex-start;gap:1.5rem;flex-wrap:wrap;">
        <div style="display:flex;height:3rem;width:3rem;min-width:3rem;align-items:center;justify-content:center;border-radius:0.5rem;background:#dbeafe;color:#2563eb;flex-shrink:0;" aria-hidden="true">
          <svg fill="none" viewBox="0 0 24 24" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2"><path d="M8 9a4 4 0 1 1 4 4v2"/><circle cx="12" cy="19" r="1" fill="currentColor"/></svg>
        </div>
        <div style="flex:1;min-width:200px;">
          <h3 style="font-size:1.1rem;font-weight:700;color:#1e40af;margin-bottom:0.5rem;">Not Sure If I Can Help? Just Ask.</h3>
          <p style="color:#1e40af;font-size:0.9rem;line-height:1.75;margin:0;">If your device isn't on the list above, reach out anyway. Describe what you have and what's wrong with the screen and I'll let you know quickly whether it's something I can take on. The answer is yes more often than you'd expect.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- CTA -->
  <section style="background:linear-gradient(135deg,#1e40af,#2563eb);padding:4rem 1.5rem;text-align:center;">
    <div style="max-width:40rem;margin:0 auto;">
      <h2 style="font-size:2rem;font-weight:800;color:white;margin-bottom:1rem;">Got a Broken Screen?</h2>
      <p style="color:#bfdbfe;font-size:1.1rem;line-height:1.75;margin-bottom:2rem;">Reach out and tell me what you've got. I'll look up the part, give you an honest quote, and let you know if it makes sense to fix.</p>
      <div style="display:flex;flex-wrap:wrap;justify-content:center;gap:1rem;">
        <a href="/contact" style="display:inline-flex;align-items:center;gap:0.5rem;background:white;color:#2563eb;font-weight:700;padding:0.875rem 2rem;border-radius:0.5rem;text-decoration:none;font-size:1rem;">
          <svg style="height:1.25rem;width:1.25rem;" fill="none" viewBox="0 0 24 24" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" aria-hidden="true"><path d="M4 4h16c1.1 0 2 .9 2 2v12c0 1.1-.9 2-2 2H4c-1.1 0-2-.9-2-2V6c0-1.1.9-2 2-2z"/><polyline points="22,6 12,13 2,6"/></svg>
          Get in Touch
        </a>
        <a href="tel:+18022341552" style="display:inline-flex;align-items:center;gap:0.5rem;background:rgba(255,255,255,0.15);color:white;font-weight:600;padding:0.875rem 2rem;border-radius:0.5rem;text-decoration:none;font-size:1rem;border:1px solid rgba(255,255,255,0.3);">
          <svg style="height:1.25rem;width:1.25rem;" fill="none" viewBox="0 0 24 24" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" aria-hidden="true"><path d="M22 16.92v3a2 2 0 0 1-2.18 2 19.79 19.79 0 0 1-8.63-3.07A19.5 19.5 0 0 1 4.69 12a19.79 19.79 0 0 1-3.07-8.67A2 2 0 0 1 3.6 1.28h3a2 2 0 0 1 2 1.72c.127.96.361 1.903.7 2.81a2 2 0 0 1-.45 2.11L7.91 8.96a16 16 0 0 0 6.29 6.29l.54-.54a2 2 0 0 1 2.11-.45c.907.339 1.85.573 2.81.7A2 2 0 0 1 21.28 17z"/></svg>
          (802) 234-1552
        </a>
      </div>
      <p style="color:#bfdbfe;font-size:0.875rem;margin-top:1.5rem;">
        <a href="/services" style="color:#bfdbfe;text-decoration:underline;" aria-label="Back to all services">← Back to All Services</a>
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

</Layout>

<style>
  .service-item {
    background: white;
    border: 1px solid #e5e7eb;
    border-radius: 0.75rem;
    padding: 1.25rem 1.5rem;
    display: flex;
    align-items: flex-start;
    gap: 1.25rem;
  }

  .service-num {
    height: 3rem;
    width: 3rem;
    min-width: 3rem;
    border-radius: 0.5rem;
    display: flex;
    align-items: center;
    justify-content: center;
    flex-shrink: 0;
  }

  .service-num svg {
    height: 1.5rem;
    width: 1.5rem;
  }

  .item-title {
    font-size: 1rem;
    font-weight: 700;
    color: #111827;
    margin-bottom: 0.375rem;
  }

  .item-desc {
    font-size: 0.9rem;
    color: #4b5563;
    line-height: 1.7;
    margin: 0;
  }

  .limit-item {
    background: white;
    border: 1px solid #e5e7eb;
    border-radius: 0.75rem;
    padding: 1.25rem 1.5rem;
    display: flex;
    align-items: flex-start;
    gap: 1rem;
  }

  .limit-icon {
    display: flex;
    height: 2.5rem;
    width: 2.5rem;
    min-width: 2.5rem;
    align-items: center;
    justify-content: center;
    border-radius: 0.5rem;
    background-color: #dbeafe;
    color: #2563eb;
    flex-shrink: 0;
  }

  .limit-icon svg {
    height: 1.25rem;
    width: 1.25rem;
  }

  .limit-item h3 {
    font-size: 0.95rem;
    font-weight: 700;
    color: #111827;
    margin-bottom: 0.25rem;
  }

  .limit-item p {
    font-size: 0.875rem;
    color: #6b7280;
    line-height: 1.6;
    margin: 0;
  }

  @media (max-width: 640px) {
    .service-item {
      flex-direction: column;
      gap: 0.75rem;
    }
    .limit-item {
      flex-direction: column;
      gap: 0.5rem;
    }
    div[style*="grid-template-columns:1fr 1fr"] {
      grid-template-columns: 1fr !important;
    }
  }
</style>